  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Toast the bread. Meanwhile, peel the garlic clove. As each piece\nof toast is ready, rub it on one side with the garlic, then spread\nwith a big spoonful of Greek yogurt and put onto plates."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get a large frying pan over a super high heat and drizzle in a\ngood glug of olive oil. Chuck in the cherry tomatoes and season\nwith salt and black pepper. Fry for 2 minutes until the tomatoes\njust begin to burst. Stir in the harissa paste to taste, then remove\nfrom the heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Spoon the hot tomatoes over the cool yoghurt toasts, making sure\nto spoon over all the flavoured oil from the pan too. Finely grate a\nlittle lemon zest over each plate of bruschetta and tear over a few\nbasil leaves to finish."
    }
  ],
